textAfterTable: User Provided tested SIM pictures AT&T 3G 71234 D Base on community post: The 71324 is the SKU for the AT&T latest UICC. The 2022 is the Vendor and Version number. Some cards the vendor numbers are  2 - G&D 3 - Gemalto 4 - Oberthur Usually user will get CME ERROR 13 (sim failure), rather than CME ERROR 10 (sim not inserted) when 3G SIM not working. CME ERROR: 32 is Network not allowed, emergency calls only, might because the card not activated.
